public enum Strategy extends Enum<Strategy>
Enum Strategy contains all strategies implemented within Duelo Maestro bot.

  • Enum Constant Summary

    Enum Constants
    Enum Constant
    Description
    BERSERK
    BERSERK strategy piles up some power ups and uses them repeatedly at the last fifth of the race, known as the BERSERK action.
    BOOST_MANIAC
    BOOST_MANIAC strategy behaves similarly as SAFE strategy, but uses and picks up boost power ups as often as possible.
    DESTROYER
    DESTROYER strategy piles up as many EMP as possible, then use it repeatedly to destroy opponent's car and restrict them to switch lane.
    HASTE_BERSERK
    HASTE_BERSERK strategy behaves similarly as BERSERK strategy, but uses boosts as soon as the player have them instead of waiting until the last fifth of the race.
    HASTE_SKIPPER
    HASTE_SKIPPER strategy behaves similarly as SKIPPER strategy, but prefers to boost instead of using lizard.
    POWER_UP_MANIAC
    POWER_UP_MANIAC strategy uses and picks up any power up as often as possible.
    RAGE
    RAGE strategy damages opponent car as often as possible.
    SAFE
    SAFE strategy picks and uses power ups wisely.
    SKIPPER
    SKIPPER strategy behaves similarly as SAFE strategy, but prefers lizard among any other power ups.
    ULTRA_BERSERK
    ULTRA_BERSERK strategy behaves similarly as BERSERK strategy, but picks up power ups more often and berserk at the last half of the race instead of the last fifth.

  • Enum Constant Details

    • SAFE

      public static final Strategy SAFE
      SAFE strategy picks and uses power ups wisely. This strategy prefers using power ups than picking them, and prefers picking power ups than accelerating or randomly switch lane without searching for power ups.

    • BERSERK

      public static final Strategy BERSERK
      BERSERK strategy piles up some power ups and uses them repeatedly at the last fifth of the race, known as the BERSERK action.

    • RAGE

      public static final Strategy RAGE
      RAGE strategy damages opponent car as often as possible. This strategy prefers picking up EMP and TWEET power ups among the others. This strategy also uses other power ups wisely.

    • BOOST_MANIAC

      public static final Strategy BOOST_MANIAC
      BOOST_MANIAC strategy behaves similarly as SAFE strategy, but uses and picks up boost power ups as often as possible.

    • POWER_UP_MANIAC

      public static final Strategy POWER_UP_MANIAC
      POWER_UP_MANIAC strategy uses and picks up any power up as often as possible.

    • ULTRA_BERSERK

      public static final Strategy ULTRA_BERSERK
      ULTRA_BERSERK strategy behaves similarly as BERSERK strategy, but picks up power ups more often and berserk at the last half of the race instead of the last fifth.

    • HASTE_BERSERK

      public static final Strategy HASTE_BERSERK
      HASTE_BERSERK strategy behaves similarly as BERSERK strategy, but uses boosts as soon as the player have them instead of waiting until the last fifth of the race.

    • DESTROYER

      public static final Strategy DESTROYER
      DESTROYER strategy piles up as many EMP as possible, then use it repeatedly to destroy opponent's car and restrict them to switch lane.

    • SKIPPER

      public static final Strategy SKIPPER
      SKIPPER strategy behaves similarly as SAFE strategy, but prefers lizard among any other power ups.

    • HASTE_SKIPPER

      public static final Strategy HASTE_SKIPPER
      HASTE_SKIPPER strategy behaves similarly as SKIPPER strategy, but prefers to boost instead of using lizard.
